HEADWORD: Chitterling
<hw>Chit"ter*ling</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The frill to the
breast of a shirt, which when ironed out resembled the small entrails.
See <er>Chitterlings</er>.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Gascoigne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

